{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 03:51:42.918787", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nOverall assessment\n- The fabric’s EBGP control plane is largely healthy: all inter-router links are up, and BGP sessions between leaves, spines, and the super-spine are established and exchanging many prefixes as expected.\n- A specific anomaly affects reachability to subnet 10.0.1.0/24 (host pc_0_1). That prefix is not present in the fabric’s BGP tables, causing inter-subnet traffic to 10.0.1.x to fail.\n\nObserved symptoms and tests\n- Data plane:\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1 (10.0.0.2 → 10.0.1.2) ping fails with “From 10.0.0.1 Destination Net Unreachable,” which is an ICMP error generated by leaf_router_0_0 (10.0.0.1). This indicates leaf_router_0_0 lacks a route to 10.0.1.0/24.\n  - pc_0_1 → pc_0_0 ping command did not complete in time; given the reverse-path issue, even if transmitted, replies would be blackholed at leaf_router_0_0.\n- Control plane and routing:\n  - leaf_router_0_0 routing table includes many 10.x/24 BGP routes but is missing 10.0.1.0/24. Hence the ICMP “net unreachable” returned by 10.0.0.1.\n  - leaf_router_0_1 routing table correctly shows 10.0.1.0/24 as directly connected and has a BGP-learned route to 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.1.2, indicating BGP sessions are up and receiving other prefixes.\n  - On both spines, “show ip bgp 10.0.1.0/24” returns “% Network not in table,” confirming the 10.0.1.0/24 prefix is not advertised into the fabric.\n  - BGP neighbor summaries show sessions are established on all involved routers (peers up with PfxRcd/Sent), so the control-plane transport is functioning.\n\nFault localization\n- The issue localizes to leaf_router_0_1 (the leaf for 10.0.1.0/24).\n  - leaf_router_0_1 FRR configuration is missing an advertisement for its local subnet. Its running configuration has no “network 10.0.1.0/24” under IPv4 unicast (and no redistribute connected), while leaf_router_0_0 properly includes “network 10.0.0.0/24.”\n  - As a result, 10.0.1.0/24 is not present in the BGP RIB of leaf_router_0_1 (verified by “% Network not in table” when queried) and is not propagated upstream to spines/super-spine.\n\nRoot cause\n- Misconfiguration on leaf_router_0_1: the 10.0.1.0/24 prefix (the host subnet for pc_0_1) is not being advertised into BGP (missing “network 10.0.1.0/24” under address-family ipv4 unicast or equivalent redistribution). This prevents all other subnets from learning a route to 10.0.1.0/24, leading to network-unreachable errors at the source leaf.\n\nImpact scope\n- All inter-subnet traffic destined to 10.0.1.0/24 is unreachable from the rest of the fabric.\n- Traffic from 10.0.1.0/24 toward other subnets may be forwarded out (since leaf_router_0_1 knows routes to others), but return traffic will fail due to missing reverse path (as observed from 10.0.0.0/24).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 48777, "output_tokens": 3897, "total_tokens": 52674, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 47744}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3072}}}
